This paper is about end-to-end dialog systems, which are typically studied in the field of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically in the subfield of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with named entity recognition, which is a task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves the use of memory networks, which are a type of neural network architecture that has been studied in the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE).
